# Documentation standards

Apply these rules when creating or editing documentation in this repository.

## Structure

1. **Hierarchy** — Place documents under `docs/` by purpose:
   - `start/` — entry and routing only
   - `paths/` — how to work (agent, Codespaces, CI-only, local)
   - `bootstrap/` — cluster creation
   - `operations/` — run, verify, upgrade, alert
   - `delivery/` — CI integration and release promotion
   - `reference/` — architecture, scripts, GitOps config, project status
   - `applications/` — application-specific docs

2. **Index** — `docs/README.md` is the sole navigation index. Do not duplicate its tables in other files.

3. **Single source of truth** — Each topic has one owner document. Other pages link to it; do not copy command blocks, workflow tables, or install-order tables.

## Writing style

- **Formal tone** — Use complete sentences. Prefer "Configure the variable" over "Just set this."
- **Scope first** — Open with one paragraph stating audience, prerequisites, and what the page covers.
- **Imperative steps** — Numbered or bulleted procedures for actions; tables for reference data.
- **No duplication** — If content exists in another doc, link with a relative path (e.g. `[verify](../operations/verify.md)`).
- **No marketing** — Avoid superlatives and filler. State facts and procedures.

## Navigation

Every document must include:

- **Prerequisites** (when non-obvious)
- **Related documents** — "See also" or "Next steps" with links at the end
- **Correct relative links** — From `docs/applications/foo.md`, link to `../operations/verify.md`, not flat `verify.md`

## Naming

- **Filenames** — kebab-case lowercase only (`aws-quickstart.md`, not `QUICKSTART.md`)
- **Titles** — Title Case in the H1; match the filename topic
- **Path labels** — Use consistent names: Cloud Agent (default), Codespaces (Option A), CI-only (Option B)

## Code and commands

- Show full commands; do not omit required flags
- State which directory to run from when not repo root
- Document environment variables in tables where multiple are required

## When adding a new document

1. Choose the correct subdirectory (do not add flat files under `docs/`)
2. Add one row to the appropriate section in `docs/README.md`
3. Link from the relevant path or operations page — not from `start/getting-started.md` command blocks
4. Do not repeat platform install order; link to `reference/architecture.md`

## Anti-patterns (do not)

- Duplicate golden-path command blocks in `start/getting-started.md`
- List the same CI workflow table in more than one file (owner: `paths/ci-only.md` or `delivery/release-pipeline.md`)
- Mislabel bootstrap mechanics as "AWS manual Terraform" (owner: `bootstrap/mechanics.md`)
- Create orphan pages with no inbound link from `docs/README.md`
